<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-964] no-cache directives with field names are transmitted downstream</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-964</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>&amp;quot;Field names MUST NOT be included with the no-cache directive in a request.&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec14.html#sec14.9.4&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec14.html#sec14.9.4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Currently, the cache implementation allows a request containing something like:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Cache-Control: no-cache=&amp;quot;Content-Location&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
to be passed downstream towards the origin.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This is another one of those tricky situations where our client has passed us a non-compliant request.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
